Feature: Merge individual feature files cucumber reports

    As Xray Connector,
    I want to merge individual feature files test execution reports
    generated by Test Automation Framework into a single report
    So that it may be uploaded into Xray

    # Rules:
    #
    # 1) Individual feature files reports should be looked for in the feature files reports directory
    # 2) The merged report should be stored in the merged report directory
    # 3) The merged report should be named merged-output.json
    # 4) The merged report may be generated several times and overwritten
    # 5) The merged report directory should be created if necessary
    # 6) The merged report directory may be a subdirectory of the feature files reports directory
    # 7) The feature files reports directory may be a subdirectory of the merged report directory

    Scenario: Merge some feature reports

        Given The feature files reports directory is 'test/fixtures/reports/features'
        And   The merged report directory is 'tmp/cucumber/reports/merged'
        And   Directory 'tmp/cucumber/reports/merged' does not exist
        When  Xray Connector merges individual feature files test execution reports
        Then  Directory 'tmp/cucumber/reports/merged' should exist
        And   File 'tmp/cucumber/reports/merged/merged-output.json' should exist

    Scenario: Merging feature reports when merged report already exists

        Given The feature files reports directory is 'test/fixtures/reports/features'
        And   The merged report directory is 'tmp/cucumber/reports/merged'
        And   A merged report has been generated in 'tmp/cucumber/reports/merged'
        When  Xray Connector merges individual feature files test execution reports
        Then  File 'tmp/cucumber/reports/merged/merged-output.json' should exist

